'''Cassin's flycatcher''' ('''''Muscicapa cassini'''''), also known as '''Cassin's grey flycatcher''' or '''Cassin's alseonax''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Muscicapidae]].  It is native to the [[Tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forests|African tropical rainforest]].
Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical [[swamp]]s.

